HEADWORD: Exhume
<hw>Ex*hume"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Exhumed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>.
<conjf>Exhuming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[LL. <ets>exhumare</ets>; L.
<ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>humus</ets> ground, soil: cf. F.
<ets>exhumer</ets>. See <er>Humble</er>.]</ety> <def>To dig out of the
ground; to take out of a place of burial; to disinter.</def>
<rj><au>Mantell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

